Photos by @_joannademarco / Kouame, whose name has been changed because of his immigration status, sits on his bed months after leaving an immigration detention center. He says that now that he has left, he feels liberated. The second image is Kouame’s Maltese dictionary, which he says he would use to look up the names he was called by the guards. The first word he looked up fell under ‘X’ - ‘Xadin,’ which is Maltese for ‘monkey.’ During the pandemic, reports emerged of inhumane conditions in detention centers. Hundreds were detained for several months. Authorities have recently said that steps are being taken to improve conditions.

